=\n| fullname       = Andr\u00e9 Wilhelm\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1943|2|7|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Gosselming]], France\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| height         =\n| weight         =\n| currentteam    =\n| discipline     =\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      =\n| amateuryears1  =\n| amateurteam1   =\n| proyears1      =\n| proteam1       =\n| majorwins      =\n| medaltemplates =\n| show-medals    =\n| updated        =\n}}\n'''Andr\u00e9 Wilhelm''' (born 7 February 1943) is a former French [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]].<ref name=\"CyclingArchives\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=9783 |title=Andr\u00e9 Wilhelm |accessdate=23 April 2014 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref> His sporting career began with VC Metz.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Livre d`Or 1976-77|last=|first=|publisher=Miroir du Cyclisme|year=1977|isbn=|location=Paris|pages=52}}</ref> He finished in [[Lanterne rouge|last place]] in the [[1969 Tour de France]].<ref name=\"ProCycling\">{{cite web |url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider.php?id=172158 |title=Andr\u00e9 Wilhelm |accessdate=23 April 2014 |work=ProCyclingStats}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|9783}}\n\n{{Tour de France Lanterne Rouge |state=collapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wilhelm, Andre}}\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Moselle (department)]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n\n{{France-cycling-bio-1940s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9_Wilhelm"}
{"title_page": "Wide Awake!", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Wide Awaaaaake!\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Parquet Courts]]\n| cover      = Wide Awake Parquet Courts.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = May 18, 2018\n| recorded   = [[Sonic Ranch]]<br>([[Tornillo, Texas]])<br>[[Electric Lady Studios]]<br>(New York City)\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Indie rock]]<ref name=\"DIY\"/>|[[post-punk revival]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.treblezine.com/reviews/parquet-courts-wide-awake-review/ |title = Parquet Courts : Wide Awake!}}</ref>|[[dance-punk]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/parquet-courts-wide-awake |title = Review: Parquet Courts, Wide Awake!}}</ref>|[[punk rock]]<ref name=\"Variety\"/>}}\n| length     = 38:37\n| language   = English\n| label      = [[Rough Trade Records|Rough Trade]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Parquet Courts Wide Awake!|url=https://www.roughtrade.com/us/music/parquet-courts-wide-awake|website=[[Rough Trade Records|Rough Trade]]|accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n| producer   = [[Danger Mouse (musician)|Danger Mouse]]\n| prev_title = [[Milano (album)|Milano]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Wide Awake!\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Almost Had to Start a Fight/In and Out of Patience\n | single1date = February 22, 2018\n | single2     = Wide Awake\n | single2date = March 8, 2018\n | single3     = Mardi Gras Beads\n | single3date = April 30, 2018\n | single4     = Total Football\n | single4date = June 8, 2018\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Wide Awake!''''' (stylized as '''''Wide Awaaaaake!''''') is the sixth studio album by American [[indie rock]] band [[Parquet Courts]], released on May 18, 2018 on [[Rough Trade Records]].\n\nThe album was preceded by the singles \"Almost Had to Start a Fight/In and Out of Patience\", \"Wide Awake\", and \"Mardi Gras Beads\", and succeeded by the single \"Total Football\".\n\n==Background==\nThe album was first announced in February 2018, while the album was recorded in December 2017 to January 2018. The band recruited [[Danger Mouse (musician)|Danger Mouse]] to produce the album, as the band claimed, as a way to push themselves outside of their comfort zone. On recruiting Danger Mouse for the album, Andrew Savage said, \"I personally liked the fact that I was writing a record that indebted to punk and funk, and Brian\u2019s a pop producer who\u2019s made some very polished records. I liked that it didn\u2019t make sense.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Kaye|first=Ben|title=Parquet Courts announce new album, Wide Awake!, produced by Danger Mouse|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/02/parquet-courts-announce-new-album-wide-awake-produced-by-danger-mouse/|website=[[Consequence of Sound]]|accessdate=May 20, 2018|date=February 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn an interview with ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', Andrew Savage described the album having a funk influence saying, \"there's this duality between joy and anger that I find to be really interesting, and that's something the record kind of deals with at large. I always thought it was really interesting how hardcore could be such an angry music form but could make you feel so positive. There's a lot of moments on the record when all of us are singing at the same time and I guess that's something I kind of associate with hardcore, or Funkadelic.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Enis|first=Eli|title=Parquet Courts on Resisting Nihilism & Why Working With Kids Was 'Pretty Scary'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/8456255/parquet-courts-interview-wide-awake|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=Lynne Segall|accessdate=May 20, 2018|date=May 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| ADM = 8.3/10<ref name=\"ADM\">{{cite web|title=Wide Awake! by Parquet Courts reviews|url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/9339/Parquet-Courts-Wide-Awake.aspx|publisher=[[AnyDecentMusic?]]|accessdate=June 19, 2018}}</ref>\n| MC = 82/100<ref name=\"MC\">{{cite web|title=Wide Awake! by Parquet Courts Reviews and Tracks|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/wide-awake!/parquet-courts|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{rating|3.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last=Sendra|first=Tim|title=Wide Awake! \u2013 Parquet Courts|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/wide-awake%21-mw0003154934|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev2Score = B+<ref>{{cite web|last=Adamczyk|first=Laura|title=Parquet Courts, Wide Awake!|url=https://music.avclub.com/parquet-courts-stephen-malkmus-and-more-albums-to-kno-1826084683|work=[[The A.V. Club]]|date=May 18, 2018|accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[The Independent]]''\n| rev3Score = {{rating|5|5}}<ref name=\"Independent\">{{cite web|last=Robertson|first=Derek|last2=Rentoul|first2=John|last3=Kaplan|first3=Ilana|title=Album reviews: Courtney Barnett, Parquet Courts, Charles Watson, Ray LaMontagne|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/courtney-barnett-parquet-courts-charles-watson-ray-lamontagne-album-review-roundup-a8354501.html|website=[[The Independent]]|date=May 16, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[NME]]''\n| rev4Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web|last=Homewood|first=Ben|title=Parquet Courts &ndash; 'Wide Awake!' album review|url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/parquet-courts-wide-awake-album-review-2316751|website=[[NME]]|date=May 17, 2018|accessdate=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[The Observer]]''\n| rev5Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite web|last=Mongredien|first=Phil|title=Parquet Courts: Wide Awake review \u2013 indie heroes bring in Danger Mouse|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/may/20/parquet-courts-wide-awake-review-danger-mouse|website=[[The Observer]]|date=May 20, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev6Score = 8.0/10<ref name=\"p4k\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Mike|title=Parquet Courts: Wide Awake!|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/parquet-courts-wide-awake/|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=May 21, 2018|accessdate=May 29, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]''\n| rev7Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite journal|last=Monroe|first=Jazz|title=Call to Arms|journal=[[Q (magazine)|Q]]|issue=386|date=July 2018|page=113}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev8Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\">{{cite web|last=Hermes|first=Will|authorlink=Will Hermes|title=Review: Parquet Courts' 'Wide Awake!' Is a Fun Punk-Funk Protest Record|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/review-parquet-courts-wide-awake-w520367|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=May 17, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]''\n| rev9Score = 8/10<ref>{{cite journal|last=Wray|first=Daniel Dylan|title=Parquet Courts: Wide Awake!|journal=[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]|issue=253|date=June 2018|page=33}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]''\n| rev10Score = A<ref name=\"Vice\">{{cite web|last=Christgau|first=Robert|authorlink=Robert Christgau|title=Robert Christgau on Parquet Courts' Sharp, Sinewy New Album|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/kzkxev/robert-christgau-on-parquet-courts-sharp-sinewy-new-album|website=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|date=June 9, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n''Wide Awake!'' received critical acclaim upon its release. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a normalized rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream publications, the album received an average score of 82, based on 28 reviews, indicating \"universal acclaim\".<ref name=\"MC\" /> In a five-star review, Emma Swan of ''[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]'' called the album, \"a gut-punch of an immediate classic\".<ref name=\"DIY\">{{cite web|last=Swann|first=Emma|title=Parquet Courts \u2013 Wide Awake!|url=http://diymag.com/2018/05/18/parquet-courts-wide-awake-album-review|website=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|date=May 18, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Exclaim!]]'' magazine, Vish Kanna said that ''Wide Awake!'' \"is a letter-perfect musical contemplation of modern times, where social uprisings are actually affecting positive change. It's urgent and potent music that's thought-provoking and danceable, and whose rage is measured by a pointed optimism.\"<ref name=\"Exclaim\">{{cite web|last=Kanna|first=Vish|title=Parquet Courts: Wide Awake!|url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/parquet_courts-wide_awake|website=[[Exclaim!]]|date=May 17, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref> Roy Trakin, in a rave review for ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', praised the album for its social conscience in its day and age, stating it \"may be the most [[woke]] punk-rock record since the heyday of [[the Clash]].\"<ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|last=Trakin|first=Roy|title=Album Review: Parquet Courts' 'Wide Awake'|url=https://variety.com/2018/music/reviews/parquet-courts-wide-awake-album-review-1202814360/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=May 18, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn a more mixed review, Chris Nelson of ''[[Mojo (magazine)|Mojo]]'' wrote that \"unsurprisingly, it flies the [[Wire (band)|Wire]] and [[Minutemen (band)|Minutemen]] flags high. More surprising are the occasional nods to funk and '60s bubblegum.\"<ref name=\"Mojo\">{{cite journal|last=Nelson|first=Chris|title=Parquet Courts: Wide Awake!|journal=[[Mojo (magazine)|Mojo]]|issue=295|date=June 2018|page=95}}</ref>\n\n''Wide Awake!'' was named 'album of the year' in an end-of-year list by Australian radio station ''[[Double J (radio)|Double J]]''<ref name=\"double-j-best-2018\">{{cite web |title=The 50 best albums of 2018 |url=https://www.abc.net.au/doublej/music-reads/features/the-50-best-albums-of-2018/10595676 |website=Double J |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |accessdate=16 December 2018 |ref=double-j-best-2018|date=2018-12-10 }}</ref> and the second-best album of 2018 by [[Paste (magazine)|Paste]].<ref name=\"Paste-best-2018\">{{cite web | url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/11/the-50-best-albums-of-2018.html | title=The 50 Best Albums of 2018 | publisher=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]] | date=November 26, 2018 | accessdate=November 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = Parquet Courts\n| extra_column = Lead vocals\n| title_width = \n| title1 = Total Football\n| length1 = 4:01\n| extra1 = A. Savage\n| title2 = Violence\n| length2 = 4:05\n| extra2 = A. Savage\n| title3 = Before the Water Gets Too High\n| length3 = 4:05\n| extra3 = A. Savage\n| title4 = Mardi Gras Beads\n| length4 = 2:43\n| extra4 = Brown\n| title5 = Almost Had to Start a Fight/In and Out of Patience\n| length5 = 3:14\n| extra5 = A. Savage\n| title6 = Freebird II\n| length6 = 2:55\n| extra6 = A. Savage\n| title7 = Normalization\n| length7 = 2:11\n| extra7 = A. Savage\n| title8 = Back to Earth\n| length8 = 3:54\n| extra8 = Brown\n| title9 = Wide Awake!\n| length9 = 2:38\n| extra9 = Brown, A. Savage, M. Savage, Yeaton\n| title10 = NYC Observation\n| length10 = 1:22\n| extra10 = A. Savage\n| title11 = Extinction\n| length11 = 1:41\n| extra11 = A. Savage\n| title12 = Death Will Bring Change\n| length12 = 2:42\n| extra12 = Brown\n| title13 = Tenderness\n| length13 = 3:06\n| extra13 = A. Savage\n| total_length = 38:37\n}}\n\n==Personnel<ref>{{cite web|title=Wide Awake! - Parquet Courts Credits|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/wide-awake%21-mw0003154934/credits|website=Allmusic.com|publisher=All Media|accessdate=May 20, 2018|date=May 18, 2018}}</ref>==\n===Parquet Courts===\n* Austin Brown \u2013 guitar, vocals, keyboards on \"Death Will Bring Change,\" \"Back to Earth,\" and \"Mardi Gras Beads\"\n* A. Savage \u2013 guitar, vocals, keyboards on \"Violence,\" \"Freebird II,\" \"Before the Water Gets Too High\"\n* Max Savage \u2013 percussion, vocals, synthesizer on \"Total Football\" and \"Normalization\"\n* Sean Yeaton \u2013 bass, vocals\n\n===Additional personnel===\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* Frank LoCrasto \u2013 piano on \"Tenderness\"\n* Eleanor Adams, Minelle Jeddy, Lucie Bismuth Berger, Rita Bochi, Julian Cohen, Mia Nikov, Kofi Dufu, Ava DiFelice, Caden Castro-Kudler, and Ariane Bourdain \u2013 additional vocals on \"Death Will Bring Change\" \n{{col-2}}\n* [[Danger Mouse (musician)|Danger Mouse]] \u2013 production\n* Kennie Takahashi \u2013 engineering\n* Joe LaPorta \u2013 mastering\n* Claudius Mittendorfer \u2013 mixing\n* Jonathan Schenke \u2013 engineering\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australian Albums ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2018/5/aria-chart-watch-474/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #474|publisher=auspOp|date=May 26, 2018|accessdate=May 26, 2018}}</ref>\n| 93\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|42|artist=Parquet Courts|album=Wide Awake!|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 25, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Wallonia|117|artist=Parquet Courts|album=Wide Awake!|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 25, 2018}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Heatseeker Albums ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/albums?chart=4483|title=NZ Heatseeker Albums Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=May 28, 2018|accessdate=May 25, 2018}}</ref>\n| 9\n|-\n{{album chart|Scotland|19|date=20180525|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 26, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Switzerland|64|artist=Parquet Courts|album=Wide Awake!|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 31, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UK2|27|date=20180525|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 26, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|122|artist=Parquet Courts|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 30, 2018}}\n|}\n\n==Accolades==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Publication\n! Country\n! Accolade\n! Year\n! Rank\n|-\n| ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]''\n| US\n| The 50 Best Albums of 2018<ref name=\"Paste-best-2018\" />\n| 2018\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n|-\n| ''[[Double J (radio)|Double J]]''\n| AUS\n| The 50 Best Albums of 2018<ref name=\"double-j-best-2018\" />\n| 2018\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.roughtrade.com/us/music/parquet-courts-wide-awake Wide Awake] at Rough Trade\n\n{{Parquet Courts}}\n\n[[Category:2018 albums]]\n[[Category:Parquet Courts albums]]\n[[Category:Rough Trade Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Danger Mouse (musician)]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded at Electric Lady Studios]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded at Sonic Ranch]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Wide Awaaaaake!\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Parquet Courts]]\n| cover      = Wide Awake Parquet Courts.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = May 18, 2018\n| recorded   = [[Sonic Ranch]]<br>([[Tornillo, Texas]])<br>[[Electric Lady Studios]]<br>(New York City)\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Indie rock]]<ref name=\"DIY\"/>|[[post-punk revival]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.treblezine.com/reviews/parquet-courts-wide-awake-review/ |title = Parquet Courts : Wide Awake!}}</ref>|[[dance-punk]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/parquet-courts-wide-awake |title = Review: Parquet Courts, Wide Awake!}}</ref>|[[punk rock]]<ref name=\"Variety\"/>}}\n| length     = 38:37\n| language   = English\n| label      = [[Rough Trade Records|Rough Trade]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Parquet Courts Wide Awake!|url=https://www.roughtrade.com/us/music/parquet-courts-wide-awake|website=[[Rough Trade Records|Rough Trade]]|accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n| producer   = [[Danger Mouse (musician)|Danger Mouse]]\n| prev_title = [[Milano (album)|Milano]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Wide Awake!\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Almost Had to Start a Fight/In and Out of Patience\n | single1date = February 22, 2018\n | single2     = Wide Awake\n | single2date = March 8, 2018\n | single3     = Mardi Gras Beads\n | single3date = April 30, 2018\n | single4     = Total Football\n | single4date = June 8, 2018\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Wide Awake!''''' (stylized as '''''Wide Awaaaaake!''''') is the sixth studio album by American [[indie rock]] band [[Parquet Courts]], released on May 18, 2018 on [[Rough Trade Records]].\n\nThe album was preceded by the singles \"Almost Had to Start a Fight/In and Out of Patience\", \"Wide Awake\", and \"Mardi Gras Beads\", and succeeded by the single \"Total Football\".\n\n==Background==\nThe album was first announced in February 2018, while the album was recorded in December 2017 to January 2018. The band recruited [[Danger Mouse (musician)|Danger Mouse]] to produce the album, as the band claimed, as a way to push themselves outside of their comfort zone. On recruiting Danger Mouse for the album, Andrew Savage said, \"I personally liked the fact that I was writing a record that indebted to punk and funk, and Brian\u2019s a pop producer who\u2019s made some very polished records. I liked that it didn\u2019t make sense.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Kaye|first=Ben|title=Parquet Courts announce new album, Wide Awake!, produced by Danger Mouse|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/02/parquet-courts-announce-new-album-wide-awake-produced-by-danger-mouse/|website=[[Consequence of Sound]]|accessdate=May 20, 2018|date=February 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn an interview with ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', Andrew Savage described the album having a funk influence saying, \"there's this duality between joy and anger that I find to be really interesting, and that's something the record kind of deals with at large. I always thought it was really interesting how hardcore could be such an angry music form but could make you feel so positive. There's a lot of moments on the record when all of us are singing at the same time and I guess that's something I kind of associate with hardcore, or Funkadelic.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Enis|first=Eli|title=Parquet Courts on Resisting Nihilism & Why Working With Kids Was 'Pretty Scary'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/8456255/parquet-courts-interview-wide-awake|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=Lynne Segall|accessdate=May 20, 2018|date=May 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| ADM = 8.3/10<ref name=\"ADM\">{{cite web|title=Wide Awake! by Parquet Courts reviews|url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/9339/Parquet-Courts-Wide-Awake.aspx|publisher=[[AnyDecentMusic?]]|accessdate=June 19, 2018}}</ref>\n| MC = 82/100<ref name=\"MC\">{{cite web|title=Wide Awake! by Parquet Courts Reviews and Tracks|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/wide-awake!/parquet-courts|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{rating|3.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last=Sendra|first=Tim|title=Wide Awake! \u2013 Parquet Courts|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/wide-awake%21-mw0003154934|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev2Score = B+<ref>{{cite web|last=Adamczyk|first=Laura|title=Parquet Courts, Wide Awake!|url=https://music.avclub.com/parquet-courts-stephen-malkmus-and-more-albums-to-kno-1826084683|work=[[The A.V. Club]]|date=May 18, 2018|accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[The Independent]]''\n| rev3Score = {{rating|5|5}}<ref name=\"Independent\">{{cite web|last=Robertson|first=Derek|last2=Rentoul|first2=John|last3=Kaplan|first3=Ilana|title=Album reviews: Courtney Barnett, Parquet Courts, Charles Watson, Ray LaMontagne|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/courtney-barnett-parquet-courts-charles-watson-ray-lamontagne-album-review-roundup-a8354501.html|website=[[The Independent]]|date=May 16, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[NME]]''\n| rev4Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web|last=Homewood|first=Ben|title=Parquet Courts &ndash; 'Wide Awake!' album review|url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/parquet-courts-wide-awake-album-review-2316751|website=[[NME]]|date=May 17, 2018|accessdate=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[The Observer]]''\n| rev5Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite web|last=Mongredien|first=Phil|title=Parquet Courts: Wide Awake review \u2013 indie heroes bring in Danger Mouse|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/may/20/parquet-courts-wide-awake-review-danger-mouse|website=[[The Observer]]|date=May 20, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev6Score = 8.0/10<ref name=\"p4k\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Mike|title=Parquet Courts: Wide Awake!|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/parquet-courts-wide-awake/|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=May 21, 2018|accessdate=May 29, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]''\n| rev7Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite journal|last=Monroe|first=Jazz|title=Call to Arms|journal=[[Q (magazine)|Q]]|issue=386|date=July 2018|page=113}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev8Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\">{{cite web|last=Hermes|first=Will|authorlink=Will Hermes|title=Review: Parquet Courts' 'Wide Awake!' Is a Fun Punk-Funk Protest Record|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/review-parquet-courts-wide-awake-w520367|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=May 17, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]''\n| rev9Score = 8/10<ref>{{cite journal|last=Wray|first=Daniel Dylan|title=Parquet Courts: Wide Awake!|journal=[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]|issue=253|date=June 2018|page=33}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]''\n| rev10Score = A<ref name=\"Vice\">{{cite web|last=Christgau|first=Robert|authorlink=Robert Christgau|title=Robert Christgau on Parquet Courts' Sharp, Sinewy New Album|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/kzkxev/robert-christgau-on-parquet-courts-sharp-sinewy-new-album|website=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|date=June 9, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n''Wide Awake!'' received critical acclaim upon its release. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a normalized rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream publications, the album received an average score of 82, based on 28 reviews, indicating \"universal acclaim\".<ref name=\"MC\" /> In a five-star review, Emma Swan of ''[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]'' called the album, \"a gut-punch of an immediate classic\".<ref name=\"DIY\">{{cite web|last=Swann|first=Emma|title=Parquet Courts \u2013 Wide Awake!|url=http://diymag.com/2018/05/18/parquet-courts-wide-awake-album-review|website=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|date=May 18, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Exclaim!]]'' magazine, Vish Kanna said that ''Wide Awake!'' \"is a letter-perfect musical contemplation of modern times, where social uprisings are actually affecting positive change. It's urgent and potent music that's thought-provoking and danceable, and whose rage is measured by a pointed optimism.\"<ref name=\"Exclaim\">{{cite web|last=Kanna|first=Vish|title=Parquet Courts: Wide Awake!|url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/parquet_courts-wide_awake|website=[[Exclaim!]]|date=May 17, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref> Roy Trakin, in a rave review for ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', praised the album for its social conscience in its day and age, stating it \"may be the most [[woke]] punk-rock record since the heyday of [[the Clash]].\"<ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|last=Trakin|first=Roy|title=Album Review: Parquet Courts' 'Wide Awake'|url=https://variety.com/2018/music/reviews/parquet-courts-wide-awake-album-review-1202814360/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=May 18, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn a more mixed review, Chris Nelson of ''[[Mojo (magazine)|Mojo]]'' wrote that \"unsurprisingly, it flies the [[Wire (band)|Wire]] and [[Minutemen (band)|Minutemen]] flags high. More surprising are the occasional nods to funk and '60s bubblegum.\"<ref name=\"Mojo\">{{cite journal|last=Nelson|first=Chris|title=Parquet Courts: Wide Awake!|journal=[[Mojo (magazine)|Mojo]]|issue=295|date=June 2018|page=95}}</ref>\n\n''Wide Awake!'' was named 'album of the year' in an end-of-year list by Australian radio station ''[[Double J (radio)|Double J]]''<ref name=\"double-j-best-2018\">{{cite web |title=The 50 best albums of 2018 |url=https://www.abc.net.au/doublej/music-reads/features/the-50-best-albums-of-2018/10595676 |website=Double J |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |accessdate=16 December 2018 |ref=double-j-best-2018|date=2018-12-10 }}</ref> and the second-best album of 2018 by [[Paste (magazine)|Paste]].<ref name=\"Paste-best-2018\">{{cite web | url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/11/the-50-best-albums-of-2018.html | title=The 50 Best Albums of 2018 | publisher=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]] | date=November 26, 2018 | accessdate=November 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = Parquet Courts\n| extra_column = Lead vocals\n| title_width = \n| title1 = Total Football\n| length1 = 4:01\n| extra1 = A. Savage\n| title2 = Violence\n| length2 = 4:05\n| extra2 = A. Savage\n| title3 = Before the Water Gets Too High\n| length3 = 4:05\n| extra3 = A. Savage\n| title4 = Mardi Gras Beads\n| length4 = 2:43\n| extra4 = Brown\n| title5 = Almost Had to Start a Fight/In and Out of Patience\n| length5 = 3:14\n| extra5 = A. Savage\n| title6 = Freebird II\n| length6 = 2:55\n| extra6 = A. Savage\n| title7 = Normalization\n| length7 = 2:11\n| extra7 = A. Savage\n| title8 = Back to Earth\n| length8 = 3:54\n| extra8 = A. Brown\n| title9 = Wide Awake!\n| length9 = 2:38\n| extra9 = Brown, A. Savage, M. Savage, Yeaton\n| title10 = NYC Observation\n| length10 = 1:22\n| extra10 = A. Savage\n| title11 = Extinction\n| length11 = 1:41\n| extra11 = A. Savage\n| title12 = Death Will Bring Change\n| length12 = 2:42\n| extra12 = Brown\n| title13 = Tenderness\n| length13 = 3:06\n| extra13 = A. Savage\n| total_length = 38:37\n}}\n\n==Personnel<ref>{{cite web|title=Wide Awake! - Parquet Courts Credits|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/wide-awake%21-mw0003154934/credits|website=Allmusic.com|publisher=All Media|accessdate=May 20, 2018|date=May 18, 2018}}</ref>==\n===Parquet Courts===\n* Austin Brown \u2013 guitar, vocals, keyboards on \"Death Will Bring Change,\" \"Back to Earth,\" and \"Mardi Gras Beads\"\n* A. Savage \u2013 guitar, vocals, keyboards on \"Violence,\" \"Freebird II,\" \"Before the Water Gets Too High\"\n* Max Savage \u2013 percussion, vocals, synthesizer on \"Total Football\" and \"Normalization\"\n* Sean Yeaton \u2013 bass, vocals\n\n===Additional personnel===\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* Frank LoCrasto \u2013 piano on \"Tenderness\"\n* Eleanor Adams, Minelle Jeddy, Lucie Bismuth Berger, Rita Bochi, Julian Cohen, Mia Nikov, Kofi Dufu, Ava DiFelice, Caden Castro-Kudler, and Ariane Bourdain \u2013 additional vocals on \"Death Will Bring Change\" \n{{col-2}}\n* [[Danger Mouse (musician)|Danger Mouse]] \u2013 production\n* Kennie Takahashi \u2013 engineering\n* Joe LaPorta \u2013 mastering\n* Claudius Mittendorfer \u2013 mixing\n* Jonathan Schenke \u2013 engineering\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australian Albums ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2018/5/aria-chart-watch-474/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #474|publisher=auspOp|date=May 26, 2018|accessdate=May 26, 2018}}</ref>\n| 93\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|42|artist=Parquet Courts|album=Wide Awake!|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 25, 2018}}\n|-\n{{album chart|